  "texts": [
    "These architectures are capable of generating entire documents and have fostered a surge in research contributions across a spectrum of areas, including architectural enhancements, training methodologies, context expansion, fine-tuning techniques, and the development of multi-modal LLMs [30].",
    "With their escalating size, often containing billions of parameters, LLMs have witnessed substantial performance enhancements, enabling them to excel across diverse natural language processing tasks.",
    "Nonetheless, challenges persist in terms of contextual appropriateness and text accuracy in the output generated by LLMs [31].",
    "These limitations can be attributed, in part, to outdated and biased knowledge embedded within their extensive training datasets [32].Fine-tuning has emerged as a pivotal technique for LLMs, enabling the customization of pre-trained models to suit specific tasks or domains.",
    "Indeed, while pre-trained LLMs demonstrate strong performance across a wide range of tasks, they may not always excel in specific domains with specialized requirements [33]."
  ],
